hh3cNat.name: hh3cNat

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cNat.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cNat.description: This MIB contains objects to manage configuration of NAT. There are no constraints on this MIB.

hh3cNATClearSessionSlotNo.name: hh3cNATClearSessionSlotNo
hh3cNATClearSessionSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board in which administrator wants to clear data of the session. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it. This node only supports 'set' operation. The return value of 'get' operation is meaningless.

hh3cNATBLConnectHighValue.name: hh3cNATBLConnectHighValue
hh3cNATBLConnectHighValue.description: The maximal connection amount. If the connection amount exceeds the value, the IP address will be added into blacklist. The IP address will not be removed from blacklist until the connection amount is less than the minimal connection amount.

hh3cNATBLConnectHighRate.name: hh3cNATBLConnectHighRate
hh3cNATBLConnectHighRate.description: The maximal connection rate(in second). If the connection rate exceed the value, the IP address will be added into blacklist. The IP address will not be removed from blacklist until the connection rate is less than the minimal connection rate.

hh3cNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate.name: hh3cNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate
hh3cNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate.description: The maximal special connection rate(in second). When administrator wants to control the speed of connection, he can selects the connection speed rate or special connection rate.

hh3cNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate.name: hh3cNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate
hh3cNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate.description: The minimal special connection rate(in second).

hh3cNATBLConnectSumEnable.name: hh3cNATBLConnectSumEnable
hh3cNATBLConnectSumEnable.description: Enable or disable the connection amount control.

hh3cNATBLConnectRateEnable.name: hh3cNATBLConnectRateEnable
hh3cNATBLConnectRateEnable.description: Enable or disable the connection rate control.

hh3cNATNPAgingTime.name: hh3cNATNPAgingTime
hh3cNATNPAgingTime.description: There are two kinds of aging time in NP. One is fast and the other is slow. Administrator can select one or other. The defalult is fast.

hh3cNATPoolInfoTable.name: hh3cNATPoolInfoTable
hh3cNATPoolInfoTable.description: NAT address pool table : The address in the pool is the IP address in the global network. The pool can span 255 IP addresses.All address pools configured by administrator are recorded in this table.

hh3cNATPoolInfoEntry.name: hh3cNATPoolInfoEntry
hh3cNATPoolInfoEntry.description: The entry of NAT address pool table.

hh3cNATPoolIdx.name: hh3cNATPoolIdx
hh3cNATPoolIdx.description: Index of the address pool: The index uniquely indicates the address pool in the system, and its range is from 1 to 320.

hh3cNATPoolStartIpAddr.name: hh3cNATPoolStartIpAddr
hh3cNATPoolStartIpAddr.description: The start IP address of address pool: It must be less than or equal to the end IP address.

hh3cNATPoolEndIpAddr.name: hh3cNATPoolEndIpAddr
hh3cNATPoolEndIpAddr.description: The end IP address of address pool: It must be more than or equal to the start IP address.

hh3cNATPoolSlotNo.name: hh3cNATPoolSlotNo
hh3cNATPoolSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board to which the address pool is bound. The address translation is processed by this NAT board . The relation between address pool and slotNo is n:1. When the address pool is not bound to the NAT board,the value is 255.

hh3cNATPoolRefCounter.name: hh3cNATPoolRefCounter
hh3cNATPoolRefCounter.description: The counter of reference. A address pool can be associated with more than one ACL and the counter of reference is recorded in this field. When the address pool is not associated with ACL, the value is 0.

hh3cNATPoolRowStatus.name: hh3cNATPoolRowStatus
hh3cNATPoolRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hh3cNATPoolIdx, hh3cNATPoolStartIpAddr and hh3cNATPoolEndIpAddr were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hh3cNATOutboundTable.name: hh3cNATOutboundTable
hh3cNATOutboundTable.description: NAT out bound table: through associating ACL number, address pool with NAT board, administrator can designate which inside IP address can be translated to global IP address in the pool and the translation is processed by which NAT board.

hh3cNATOutboundEntry.name: hh3cNATOutboundEntry
hh3cNATOutboundEntry.description: The entry of NAT out bound table.

hh3cNATOutboundAclNo.name: hh3cNATOutboundAclNo
hh3cNATOutboundAclNo.description: The number of ACL(Access Control List). When the packet accords with the rule in the ACL, its source IP address will be translated to IP address in Address pool.

hh3cNATOutboundPoolIdx.name: hh3cNATOutboundPoolIdx
hh3cNATOutboundPoolIdx.description: The index of address pool in hh3cNATPoolInfoTable. when administrator doesn't use the address pool and use the IP address of the interface as the address of global network, the value is 2147483647.

hh3cNATOutboundIsNoPat.name: hh3cNATOutboundIsNoPat
hh3cNATOutboundIsNoPat.description: Whether to use no pat manner. The translation of no pat is that the translation doesn't use the port information of packet.

hh3cNATOutboundSlotNo.name: hh3cNATOutboundSlotNo
hh3cNATOutboundSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

hh3cNATOutboundRowStatus.name: hh3cNATOutboundRowStatus
hh3cNATOutboundRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hh3cNATOutboundAclNo or hh3cNATOutboundAclNo and hh3cNATOutboundPoolIdx were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hh3cNATServerTable.name: hh3cNATServerTable
hh3cNATServerTable.description: NAT inside Server Table. Administrator can configure server in the private network which can provide service for people in the public network. The translation map is : (InsideIP , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort ) (InsideIP + 1 , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort + 1) (InsideIP + 2 , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort + 2) ... ... ... (InsideIP+n(=InsideIP2),InsidePort--> GlobalIP,GlobalPort+n(=GlobalPort2))

hh3cNATServerEntry.name: hh3cNATServerEntry
hh3cNATServerEntry.description: The entry of NAT inside server table.

hh3cNATServerProType.name: hh3cNATServerProType
hh3cNATServerProType.description: The type of protocol: icmp(1), tcp(6), udp(17) and others.

hh3cNATServerGlobalIP.name: hh3cNATServerGlobalIP
hh3cNATServerGlobalIP.description: The global IP address of Inside Server.

hh3cNATServerStartGlobalPort.name: hh3cNATServerStartGlobalPort
hh3cNATServerStartGlobalPort.description: The start global port of Inside Server. When the port need not be configured, the value is 0.

hh3cNATServerEndGlobalPort.name: hh3cNATServerEndGlobalPort
hh3cNATServerEndGlobalPort.description: The end global port of Inside Server. When administrator doesn't configure a series of inside server, the value is 0. If the value is not zero, the value of (GlobalPort2-GlobalPort) must be equal to (InsideIP2 - InsideIP).

hh3cNATServerStartInsideIP.name: hh3cNATServerStartInsideIP
hh3cNATServerStartInsideIP.description: The start private IP address of Inside Server.

hh3cNATServerEndInsideIP.name: hh3cNATServerEndInsideIP
hh3cNATServerEndInsideIP.description: The end private IP address of Inside Server. When administrator doesn't configure a series of inside server, the value is 0.0.0.0.

hh3cNATServerInsidePort.name: hh3cNATServerInsidePort
hh3cNATServerInsidePort.description: The private port of Inside Server.

hh3cNATServerSlotNo.name: hh3cNATServerSlotNo
hh3cNATServerSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

hh3cNATServerAclNumber.name: hh3cNATServerAclNumber
hh3cNATServerAclNumber.description: Number of basic or advanced acl.

hh3cNATServerRowStatus.name: hh3cNATServerRowStatus
hh3cNATServerRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hh3cNATServerProType, hh3cNATServerGlobalIP, hh3cNATServerGlobalPort and hh3cNATServerInsideIP were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hh3cNATTimeOutTable.name: hh3cNATTimeOutTable
hh3cNATTimeOutTable.description: NAT Time out Table. When a connection is established, if there are not any actives in this connection between the time, it will be disconnected.

hh3cNATTimeOutEntry.name: hh3cNATTimeOutEntry
hh3cNATTimeOutEntry.description: The entry of NAT Time out Table.

hh3cNATBLEnableTable.name: hh3cNATBLEnableTable
hh3cNATBLEnableTable.description: NAT blacklist function Enable Table. In this table, administrator can decide whether to start the function of blacklist in the NAT board. When the function of blacklist can't be set for a NAT board, the number of NAT board is 256.

hh3cNATBLEnableEntry.name: hh3cNATBLEnableEntry
hh3cNATBLEnableEntry.description: The entry of NAT blacklist Enable Table.

hh3cNATBLEnableSlotNo.name: hh3cNATBLEnableSlotNo
hh3cNATBLEnableSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. When the function of blacklist can't be set for a NAT board, the value is 255.

hh3cNATBLEnable.name: hh3cNATBLEnable
hh3cNATBLEnable.description: Start or stop of function of balcklist.

hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable.name: hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable
hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable.description: The table of connection control of special IP address. In this table, administrator can decide to adopt which manner to control the connection which IP address is the special IP address.

hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry.name: hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry
hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry.description: The entry of the table of connection control of special IP address.

hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP.name: hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP
hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP.description: The special IP address. The IP is private IP address.

hh3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue.name: hh3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue
hh3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue.description: The maximal connection amount. It must be more than the minimal connection amount.

hh3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue.name: hh3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue
hh3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue.description: The minimal connection amount. It must be less than the maximal connection amount.

hh3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate.name: hh3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate
hh3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate.description: Whether to use the special connection rate control.

hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus.name: hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus
hh3cNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hh3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue, hh3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue and hh3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hh3cNATBLManagerTable.name: hh3cNATBLManagerTable
hh3cNATBLManagerTable.description: The management table of blacklist. The table doesn't support 'getnext' operation.

hh3cNATBLManagerEntry.name: hh3cNATBLManagerEntry
hh3cNATBLManagerEntry.description: The entry of management table of blacklist.

hh3cNATBLIpAdress.name: hh3cNATBLIpAdress
hh3cNATBLIpAdress.description: The IP address of entry of blacklist.

hh3cNATBLConSpd.name: hh3cNATBLConSpd
hh3cNATBLConSpd.description: The state of connection rate: red(1) : the connection rate is above the upper limit. yellow(2): the connection rate is between the upper and lower limit. green(3) : the conneciton rate is below the lower limit.

hh3cNATStatTable.name: hh3cNATStatTable
hh3cNATStatTable.description: The statistics information table of NAT module.

hh3cNATStatEntry.name: hh3cNATStatEntry
hh3cNATStatEntry.description: The entry of statistics information table of NAT module.

hh3cNATStatNATBoardNo.name: hh3cNATStatNATBoardNo
hh3cNATStatNATBoardNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

hh3cNATStatActiveTblCount.name: hh3cNATStatActiveTblCount
hh3cNATStatActiveTblCount.description: Active PAT session count In software.

hh3cNATStatActiveTblCountInNP.name: hh3cNATStatActiveTblCountInNP
hh3cNATStatActiveTblCountInNP.description: Active PAT session count In NP.

hh3cNATStatNumOfUsedPort.name: hh3cNATStatNumOfUsedPort
hh3cNATStatNumOfUsedPort.description: The number of used port in NP.

hh3cNATStatNumOfGoodPkt.name: hh3cNATStatNumOfGoodPkt
hh3cNATStatNumOfGoodPkt.description: The number of good packet in NP.

hh3cNATStatNumOfBadPkt.name: hh3cNATStatNumOfBadPkt
hh3cNATStatNumOfBadPkt.description: The number of bad packet in NP.

hh3cNATSequenceSessionCount.name: hh3cNATSequenceSessionCount
hh3cNATSequenceSessionCount.description: Active session table count hash by private IP.

hh3cNATSessionTable.name: hh3cNATSessionTable
hh3cNATSessionTable.description: The nat session information table. There is the address translation information in the table. The sketch map of connection is pc1(private Net)------------------>NAT Device ------------------>Server(public Net) InsideIP, InsidePort---->translating to GlobalIP, GlobalPort------>PeerIP, PeerPort.

hh3cNATSessionEntry.name: hh3cNATSessionEntry
hh3cNATSessionEntry.description: The entry of session information table.

hh3cNATSessionHashNumber.name: hh3cNATSessionHashNumber
hh3cNATSessionHashNumber.description: The row number of the hash table.

hh3cNATStaticRowStatus.name: hh3cNATStaticRowStatus
hh3cNATStaticRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hh3cNATStaticInsideIp and hh3cNATStaticGlobalIp were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hh3cNATStaticEnableTable.name: hh3cNATStaticEnableTable
hh3cNATStaticEnableTable.description: Active the static Nat on interface.

hh3cNATStaticEnableEntry.name: hh3cNATStaticEnableEntry
hh3cNATStaticEnableEntry.description: Active the static Nat on interface.

hh3cNATStaticEnable.name: hh3cNATStaticEnable
hh3cNATStaticEnable.description: Enable/disable the static Nat on the interface(hh3cNatStaticEnableIfIndex). disable (0) enable (1)

hh3cNATDnsMapTable.name: hh3cNATDnsMapTable
hh3cNATDnsMapTable.description: This table is used to set mapping of DNS.

hh3cNATDnsMapProtocolType.name: hh3cNATDnsMapProtocolType
hh3cNATDnsMapProtocolType.description: TCP Transmission Control Protocol. UDP User Datagram Protocol.

hh3cNATDnsMapLastUseTime.name: hh3cNATDnsMapLastUseTime
hh3cNATDnsMapLastUseTime.description: Its value is the time that the device uses from startup to last use 'Dns Map'record. If the value is 0,the device never use this record.

hh3cNATDnsMapRowStatus.name: hh3cNATDnsMapRowStatus
hh3cNATDnsMapRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hh3cNATDnsMapDomainName, hh3cNATDnsMapGlobalIp and hh3cNATDnsMapGlobalPortor hh3cNATDnsMapDomainName, hh3cNATDnsMapGlobalIp, hh3cNATDnsMapGlobalPort and hh3cNATDnsMapProtocolType were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.
